data.enText: to cut words or designs on wood, stone, metal, etc.
The silver cup was engraved with his name.

data.chText: 他的名字刻在了银杯上。
data.enText: His name was engraved on the silver cup.
be engraved on/in your heart, memory, mind, etc.

data.chText: 牢记，铭记，深深印入（心中、记忆中、头脑中等）
data.enText: to be sth that you will never forget because it affected you so strongly
be engraved on/in your heart, memory, mind, etc.

data.chText: 牢记，铭记，深深印入（心中、记忆中、头脑中等）
data.enText: to be sth that you will never forget because it affected you so strongly

tr: carve, cut, or etch into a material or surface
example: engraved the trophy cupt with the winner's
the lovers scratched their names into the bark of the tree

tr: carve or cut a design or letters into
example: engrave the pen with the owner's name

tr: carve or cut into a block used for printing or print from such a block

example: The event engraved itself into her memory

value.def: If you engrave something with a design or words, or if you engrave a design or words on it, you cut the design or words into its surface.

example.ex: Your wedding ring can be engraved with a personal inscription at no extra cost...
example.tran: 可以免费在你的婚戒上刻上你的题字。

example.ex: Harrods will also engrave your child's name on the side...
example.tran: 哈罗兹还会将你孩子的名字刻在侧面。

example.ex: I'm having 'John Law' engraved on the cap.
example.tran: 我要在笔帽上刻上John Law。

gramarinfo.label: Also V n, V n with quote
